Connecting to visualize...
Yeh raha interactive guide — har tab pe click karo aur detail dekho. Neeche ek quick summary bhi hai:

map() — Array ka shape change karta hai. Har element in, har element out — count same rehta hai. [1,2,3] → [2,4,6].

filter() — Array chhota karta hai. Jo condition pass kare wo rakho, baaki hata do. [1,2,3,4,5] → [2,4] (sirf even).

reduce() — Sabse powerful. Pura array milake ek cheez banta hai — number, object, ya kuch bhi. Cart ka total? reduce. Word count? reduce.

Set — Unique values ki guarantee. Duplicates automatically nikl jaate hain. Array se duplicates hatana ho toh [...new Set(arr)] sabse aasaan tarika hai.

Map object — Regular {} object jaisa, par keys koi bhi ho sakti hain (number, object bhi). Order preserve hota hai, size property milti hai.

Ek important baat — map, filter, reduce teeno chain ho sakte hain:

js
const result = products
  .filter(p => p.inStock)       // pehle filter
  .map(p => p.name)             // phir sirf naam nikalo
  .reduce((acc, name) => acc + ', ' + name); // phir join karo
Koi bhi concept aur depth mein samajhna ho toh bata do!

