Bro developer se yeh poochho — copy karke bhej do:

Subject: CORS issue with API

Hi, I'm building a web app using your Claude API. When I call the API from browser (HTML file), I'm getting a CORS error.

Can you please add these headers to your API responses:

Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
Access-Control-Allow-Methods: GET, POST, OPTIONS
Access-Control-Allow-Headers: Content-Type, Authorization
My API call looks like this:

GET /api/ai/claude-opus-4.7/message/{message}?token={token}
Without CORS headers, browser blocks the request from frontend. Backend (Node.js/Python) se toh kaam karta hai but browser se nahi.

Ya agar developer ne Node.js/Express mein banaya hai toh use bata do:

js
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  res.header('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', '*');
  res.header('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'GET, POST, OPTIONS');
  res.header('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Content-Type');
  next();
});
Ya agar FastAPI (Python) hai:

python
from fastapi.middleware.cors import CORSMiddleware
app.add_middleware(CORSMiddleware, allow_origins=["*"])
Jab developer CORS fix kar de, website turant kaam karegi — koi change nahi chahiye website mein! 🙂

